org.bwillard.ccsf.course.cs111c.labB

Interface BookPile<B>

  • Type Parameters:
    B - Book to be implemented

    public interface BookPile<B>
    This Interface is uses some similar concepts from java.util.Stack. I.E, push, pop, and peek.
    Author:
    bradleywillard

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void clearPile()
      Removes (clears) all books (if any) from the pile.
      boolean hasBooksInPile()
      Checks the pile to see if any books exist.
      B peekTopBookOnPile()
      Peeks at and returns topmost book from the pile.
      B popTopBookFromPile()
      Pops (removes) and returns the topmost book from the pile.
      B pushBookToPile(B newBook)
      Pushes (adds) a book on top of the existing pile of books.

    • Method Detail

      • pushBookToPile

        B pushBookToPile(B newBook)
        Pushes (adds) a book on top of the existing pile of books. If no books exist in the pile, this item will be the first and last book on the pile until the next book is added (pushed). BookPile size is increased by 1
        Parameters:
        newBook - to be pushed (added) on top of the pile
        Returns:
        the item added to the pile, null otherwise

      • popTopBookFromPile

        B popTopBookFromPile()
        Pops (removes) and returns the topmost book from the pile. BookPile size is decreased by 1. Returns null, if no books exists in the pile
        Returns:
        the Book removed from the top of the pile, null otherwise

      • peekTopBookOnPile

        B peekTopBookOnPile()
        Peeks at and returns topmost book from the pile. BookPile is unaffected.
        Returns:
        Book from top of the pile, null if no books in pile

      • hasBooksInPile

        boolean hasBooksInPile()
        Checks the pile to see if any books exist.
        Returns:
        True if there is at least one book in the pile

      • clearPile

        void clearPile()
        Removes (clears) all books (if any) from the pile.
